Quick Reference

| | Latency | Throughput |
|---|---|---|
| Definition | Time for one operation to complete | Operations completed per unit time |
| Unit | ms, μs, seconds | RPS, TPS, msg/sec, GB/hr |
| "System is slow" complaint | ✅ Usually means high latency | Low throughput causes backlogs |
| Improved by | Caching, fewer hops, faster queries, async I/O | Parallelism, batching, horizontal scaling |
| Measured using | Percentiles (P50, P95, P99) | Ops/second over a time window |
| Little's Law role | W (time in system) | λ (completion rate) |

